    "clinical_pearls": [
      "Graft infection rarely cures with antibiotics alone - excision required",
      "Late infections are often indolent S. epidermidis - low-grade symptoms",
      "Herald bleed = impending aortoenteric fistula - act fast",
      "Peri-graft fluid >3 months post-op is abnormal",
      "In-situ reconstruction has better patency if infection is controlled"
